      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cpb-hemolysis-worst-case-001",
      "type": "Claim",
      "name": "CFD model reliably identifies worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under CPB conditions",
      "description": "The CFD model of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump has been demonstrated to predict relative hemolysis index (RH) with sufficient fidelity to identify worst-case operating conditions across the 5 flow-speed combinations evaluated. Validation activities confirm that the model captures the dominant shear-stress-driven hemolysis mechanisms, and mesh convergence studies establish discretization uncertainty within acceptable bounds for MRL 2. The claim scope is restricted to the COU envelope: flow rates 2–6 L/min, rotational speeds 2000–3500 RPM, and blood analogue fluid at 37°C.",
      "purpose": "Support regulatory submission demonstrating that CFD-predicted worst-case hemolysis operating point is conservative relative to the predicate device benchmark (RH < 1).",
      "scope": "FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry; CPB operating envelope; MRL 2 credibility requirements"
    }
  ],
